  "title": "Product Engineer (Advantest 93K ATE)",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>Assist in the validation and release of semiconductor products, ensuring smooth transition from design to production.</li>\n  <li>Partner with test and production teams to troubleshoot issues, support reliability testing, and drive yield improvements.</li>\n  <li>Coordinate with foundries, subcontractors, and internal stakeholders to resolve production challenges and meet delivery goals.</li>\n  <li>Prepare and present technical documentation, including test limits, correlation studies, and yield analysis reports.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma in Electronics/Electrical Engineering or equivalent.</li>\n  <li>At least 2 years of experience in Product or Test Engineering, preferably with exposure to <strong>foundry processes</strong>.</li>\n  <li>Solid understanding of <strong>digital, mixed-signal, and RF testing methodologies</strong>; hands-on experience with <strong>Advantest 93K ATE</strong>.</li>\n  <li>Proficient in <strong>data analysis</strong> and familiar with tools such as <strong>JMP, CEDA, DataPower</strong>, or <strong>Optimal+</strong>; scripting skills in <strong>Perl, Java, or VBA</strong> for automation.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you are keen to apply for the position, kindly email your detailed resume in<strong> MS Word </strong>to <strong>hr@recruit-expert.com</strong></p>\n<p>Please note that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p>\n<p>For more job opportunities, please visit our website at <a href=\"http://www.recruit-expert.com/\"><strong>www.recruit-expert.com</strong></a></p>\n<p>EA Licence: 19C9701<br>\nRegistration: R21100996</p>",
